Thank you again to our Pantone community for participating in our “Very” first “Very Peri” NFT drop inspired by our 2022 Pantone Color of the Year, 17-3938 Very Peri. 

Our goal was to explore the world of color through new avenues of digital art. As a result, free NFTs were claimed at a record speed! 

For those headed to SXSW, @polygon1993 has created four exclusive new NFTs for attendees to claim. To claim these artworks and hear about our process, visit the Pantone Very Peri room created by #tezos. For more information, please visit tezos.com/events 
We hope to see you there!

latestPosts.caption:
Color matching + walking practice turned Public Art Installation.

‘Local Color’ is an ongoing series that investigates how color shapes our sense of place. I walked across Emeryville with a @pantone book, matching swatches to found colors from spray painted sidewalks to blooming foliage and other pieces of public art.

For this series of bus shelters, each color was found along the Emery-go-round route, offering riders a fresh way to see the colors all around them.

Follow @erinlovescolors if color brings you joy 🌈

There’s a color that speaks before taste even begins.

A color you can feel, live, and remember.

It’s Verde D’Amico—a rich, vibrant shade created in collaboration with Pantone. Together, we crafted a hue that captures the essence of D’Amico: a story of wellbeing, nature, and the simple, genuine pleasure of good food.

This bold, custom color connects generations and celebrates those who truly appreciate the joy of eating well.

This is who we are.

This is Verde D’Amico.
